scrypt
------------------------------------------
A simple password-based encryption utility is available as a demonstration of
the scrypt key derivation function. On modern hardware and with default
parameters, the cost of cracking the password on a file encrypted by scrypt
enc is approximately 100 billion times more than the cost of cracking the same
password on a file encrypted by openssl enc; this means that a five-character
password using scrypt is stronger than a ten-character password using openssl.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.20-1
  libopenssl100-1.0.1e-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.23.51-1
  cygport-0.12.2-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.tarsnap.com/scrypt.html

Canonical download:
  http://www.tarsnap.com/scrypt/scrypt-1.1.6.tgz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack scrypt-1.1.6-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
         unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./scrypt-1.1.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/scrypt-1.1.6-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/scrypt-1.1.6-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(scrypt)
  /usr/bin/scrypt.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/scrypt.README
  /usr/share/doc/scrypt/FORMAT
  /usr/share/man/man1/scrypt.1.gz

------------------

